Program: Discovery
Title: The life of whales
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx9r
Last Broadcast Date: 18 January 1999
A look at the enigma of the deep-water whales, some of which have never been seen. Sperm whales are just one species of whale that can dive as deep at 7,000 ft and the blue whale is the world's largest animal.